<subSubSection id="22A66546FFA1FFEDFF11FEEC4A60FE22" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFA1FFEDFF11FEEC4A60FE22" blockId="57.[151,1436,289,782]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFF11FEEC4A15FE9A" bold="true" box="[151,278,289,314]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Etymology</emphasis>
. The genus is named for Saci-PererÃª, a character in Brazilian folklore, known to disappear and reappear wherever he wishes, as an allusion to the disrupted geographical distribution of the hard-to-find 
<typeStatus id="B507886FFFA1FFEDFA8EFE8B4E3BFEFE" box="[1288,1336,326,350]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">type</typeStatus>
species; gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="22A66546FFA1FFEDFF41FE404876FCAE" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFA1FFEDFF41FE404F88FE06" blockId="57.[151,1436,289,782]" box="[199,1163,397,422]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFF41FE404ACFFE06" bold="true" box="[199,460,397,422]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis/Description</emphasis>
. See diagnosis and description of single known species below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A0336CDFFA1FFEDFF41FE7C4876FCAE" blockId="57.[151,1436,289,782]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFF41FE7C4A09FE6A" bold="true" box="[199,266,433,458]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Notes</emphasis>
. The recent molecular phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFD2DFE7C48FFFE69" authority="(Eberle et al. 2018)" authorityName="Eberle" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Eberle" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[683,1020,433,458]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Pholcidae (
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA1FFEDFCAEFE7C48F7FE69" author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." box="[808,1012,433,458]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="141" refId="ref37668" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Eberle 
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFCFCFE7F48B0FE6A" box="[890,947,433,458]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
placed this genus/species as sister to the genera 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFE90FE1B4916FE4E" authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[278,533,469,494]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Waunana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFE90FE1B4A7CFE4D" box="[278,383,470,493]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Waunana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA1FFEDFE0EFE184916FE4E" author="Huber, B. A." box="[392,533,469,494]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFDB0FE184828FE4E" authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[566,811,469,494]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pisaboa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFDB0FE184991FE4E" box="[566,658,469,494]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Pisaboa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA1FFEDFD1AFE184828FE4E" author="Huber, B. A." box="[668,811,469,494]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with reasonable support. The three genera share (1) a distinct ventral apophysis distally on the male palpal femur (a possibly plesiomorphic character also present in several other 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFEB6FDD04AC7FD96" baseAuthorityName="Huber" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[304,452,541,566]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">Modisiminae</taxonomicName>
genera, i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFDD7FDD34840FD96" authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[593,835,541,566]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Tupigea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFDD7FDD349AFFD95" box="[593,684,542,565]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Tupigea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA1FFEDFD35FDD04840FD96" author="Huber, B. A." box="[691,835,541,566]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFCC9FDD04F72FD96" authority="Simon, 1893" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[847,1137,541,566]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Psilochorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFCC9FDD048D6FD96" box="[847,981,541,566]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Psilochorus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA1FFEDFC5BFDD04F72FD96" author="Simon, E." box="[989,1137,541,566]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="256 - 488" refId="ref39605" refString="Simon, E. (1893) Histoire Naturelle des Araignees. 1 (2). 2 nd edition. Roret, Paris, 233 pp. [pp. 256 - 488]" type="book chapter" year="1893">Simon, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFBF8FDD34A0DFDF9" authority="Chamberlin &amp; Ivie, 1938" authorityName="Chamberlin &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="1938" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Anopsicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFBF8FDD34FF2FD95" box="[1150,1265,542,565]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Anopsicus</emphasis>
Chamberlin &amp; Ivie, 1938
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFE9DFD8C4936FDF9" authority="Simon, 1893" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[283,565,577,602]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Modisimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFE9DFD8C4A95FDFA" box="[283,406,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Modisimus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0E2D4B3CFFA1FFEDFE19FD8C4936FDF9" author="Simon, E." box="[415,565,577,602]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="256 - 488" refId="ref39605" refString="Simon, E. (1893) Histoire Naturelle des Araignees. 1 (2). 2 nd edition. Roret, Paris, 233 pp. [pp. 256 - 488]" type="book chapter" year="1893">Simon, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) vertical hairs in higher than usual density on male femora and tibia or tibiae only (also widespread in 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFE7FFDA84991FDDE" baseAuthorityName="Huber" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[505,658,613,638]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">Modisiminae</taxonomicName>
); (3) a relatively long and slender procursus. 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFB17FDAB4E0BFDDD" authority="Huber &amp; Carvalho, 2019" authorityName="Huber &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2019" box="[1169,1288,614,637]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Saciperere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFB17FDAB4E0BFDDD" box="[1169,1288,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Saciperere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFAC6FDA84E9FFDDE" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1344,1436,613,638]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pisaboa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFAC6FDA84E9FFDDE" box="[1344,1436,613,638]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Pisaboa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also share the general morphology of the female internal genitalia (elongate pore plates in lateral position and membranous âreceptacleâ originating from âvalveâ area). The species below is not assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFB41FD604E20FD66" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1223,1315,685,710]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pisaboa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFB41FD604E20FD66" box="[1223,1315,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Pisaboa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it lacks the distinctive hinged apophyses on the male chelicerae characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="ADBC4D4EFFA1FFEDFB96FD1C4F6FFD4A" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1040,1132,721,746]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pisaboa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58C8EADFFFA1FFEDFB96FD1C4F6FFD4A" box="[1040,1132,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Pisaboa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has instead an equally distinctive armature of the male chelicerae (see diagnosis below).
</paragraph>
